  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Currently, post-editing is still crucial for ensuring adherence to AD production principles (e.g., Figure 2 (c)).",
    "However, we contend that future research should focus on the automation of AD generation, thereby eliminating the need for human post-editing.",
    "Automatic evaluation of ADs typically involves comparing the generated ADs to the gold standards.",
    "Classic text generation metrics are employed to assess: 1) textual relevance through N-gram overlaps (e.g., BLEU (Papineni et al., 2002), ROUGE-L (Lin, 2004), METEOR (Banerjee and Lavie, 2005), and CHRF (Popović, 2015)); or 2) embeddingbased semantic similarity between the generated and ground-truth ADs (e.g., MoverScore (Zhao et al., 2019), BERTScore (Zhang et al., 2020), BARTScore (Yuan et al., 2021), (Ref)CLIPScore (Hessel et al., 2021), EMScore (Shi et al., 2022), and (Ref)PAC-S (Sarto et al., 2023)).",
    "Given the multimodal nature of AD generation, image and video captioning metrics are also widely employed to evaluate the quality of generated ADs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Classic text generation metrics are employed to assess: 1) textual relevance through N-gram overlaps (e.g., BLEU (Papineni et al., 2002), ROUGE-L (Lin, 2004), METEOR (Banerjee and Lavie, 2005), and CHRF (Popović, 2015)); or 2) embeddingbased semantic similarity between the generated and ground-truth ADs (e.g., MoverScore (Zhao et al., 2019), BERTScore (Zhang et al., 2020), BARTScore (Yuan et al., 2021), (Ref)CLIPScore (Hessel et al., 2021), EMScore (Shi et al., 2022), and (Ref)PAC-S (Sarto et al., 2023))."
